com.tsgrp.migration.queuepop

Class QueuePopulatorExcel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.queuepop.QueuePopulatorExcel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PipelinePopulateQueueEventListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    QueuePopulatorExcelWithAssociations

    public class QueuePopulatorExcel
extends AbstractListener
implements PipelinePopulateQueueEventListener
    Queue Populator Excel is a source listener that is used to populate the queue. It reads values from an excel file specified in the configuration to populate the queue. The value that will be stored in the queue will be the unique list of values specified in the keycol in the configuration.

    MigrationNode Attributes Set

    • om_queue_id (generated)
    • om_source_id

      • processFile

        protected void processFile(MigrationPipeline pipeline,
                           MigrationQueue queue,
                           FileStoreConnection fsConnection)
                    throws org.apache.poi.openxml4j.exceptions.InvalidFormatException,
                           java.io.IOException
        Given a file, this method will create an Excel workbook and use that file's stream to build up on the queue with the information on the workbook.
        Parameters:
        pipeline - Migration pipeline used to populate the queue.
        queue - Queue that will be populated with information in Excel files.
        excelFile - Provided Excel file used to populate the queue with its nodes.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If there is an error when creating the excel workbook.
        org.apache.poi.openxml4j.exceptions.InvalidFormatException - If there is an error when creating the excel workbook.

      • processFolder

        protected void processFolder(MigrationPipeline pipeline,
                             MigrationQueue queue,
                             FileStoreConnection fsConnection,
                             java.lang.String relativeFolderPath)
                      throws java.io.IOException,
                             org.apache.poi.openxml4j.exceptions.InvalidFormatException
        Lists all the files and directories for the folder passed into the parameters, processing them to add into the queue. All files inside the given directory will be added into the queue. Any sub directories found inside the folder will be processed recursively if the flag processFoldersRecursively is set to true, and the method will call itself, passing the child directory as the new parameter.
        Parameters:
        pipeline - Migration pipeline used to populate the queue.
        queue - Queue that will be populated with information in Excel files.
        folder - Folder given to process the contents of.
        relativeFolderPath - Relative root path to the provided folder, if applicable.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown if there is an exception when processing a file to add to the queue.
        org.apache.poi.openxml4j.exceptions.InvalidFormatException - Thrown if there is an exception when processing a file to add to the queue.

      • buildQueue

        protected void buildQueue(MigrationQueue queue,
                          org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel.Workbook workbook)

      • processExcelRow

        protected void processExcelRow(MigrationQueue queue,
                               java.util.HashSet<java.lang.String> keyValueSet,
                               org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel.Row row,
                               int rowIdx)
                        throws java.text.ParseException
        This method will process the current Excel row that is being added to the queue. It will iterate through the property columns injected or defaulted by the module found on the propertyColumns variable. The method will extract the value according to the configured data type and add it to the extra properties maps used to create a new queue item. If the current row's identified source id value is unique and hasn't been added to the passed in key value set HashSet, a new queue item will be created.
        Parameters:
        queue - configured Migration Queue object
        keyValueSet - hash set used to ensure no queue items with duplicate source ids are created
        row - current row we are processing
        rowIdx - number of the row we are processing
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException - if an exception occurs for any date attribue being processed for this row

      • loadPropertiesMap

        protected void loadPropertiesMap(org.apache.poi.ss.usermodel.Sheet sheet)
        Evaluates if the injected variable propertyColumns was defined in the project configurations. If it isn't, it will evaluate the injected variable propertyRow to define which row contains the property definitions, or it will default to loading property definitions from row 0 if not defined.
        Parameters:
        sheet - Excel sheet that contains items to migrate, from which we will extract property definitions
